:{{see|carina}}

==English==
===Etymology===
Named by the French [[astronomer]] Nicolas Louis de Lacaille in 1763. From {{L.}} ''[[carina]]'', the "keel of a ship"
===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia|Carina (constellation)}}
'''Carina'''

#{{constellation}}: A [[summer]] [[constellation]] of the [[southern]] sky, said to resemble the [[keel]] of a [[ship]]. It contains the [[star]] [[Canopus]], the secnd brightest star in the night sky. Until 1763, it was part of a larger constellation, [[Argo Navis]].

